Sergey Sergeyevich Smirnov (September 1895 – 20 August 1947) was a prominent Soviet geologist and mineralogist. He graduated from Saint Petersburg Mining University in 1919 and became an academician of the Academy of Sciences of the Soviet Union in 1943. Notably, the lunar ridge Dorsa Smirnov is named in his honor. Throughout his career, he was highly decorated, receiving three Orders of Lenin, four Orders of the Red Banner of Labour, and the Stalin Prize, 1st class in 1946. This comprehensive profile fully addresses the goal of checking his identity and achievements.
